What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?

create a local repository for my project. To be able to maintain versions of my project

How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository?
What value do you think it offers?

Staging area keeps files that user want to commit in the repository seperating those files from files present in working directory that doesnot require versioning.

How can you use the staging area to make sure you have one commit per logical
change?

Add files that requires single logical changes in staging area and then doing commit to ensure one commit per logical change

What are some situations when branches would be helpful in keeping your history
organized? How would branches help?

branches keeps the original project seperated from modified version of project

How do the diagrams help you visualize the branch structure?

diagrams tell the commit from which branches are made and in each branch which is the latest commit

